All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was fixed:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```typescript
// Before (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` in the loop condition caused the loop to stop one element short, so the last item in every array was silently skipped. Removing it lets the loop run through all indices (`0` to `items.length - 1`), processing every element including the last one.

